Question: Isosceles $\triangle{ABC}$ has a right angle at $C$.  Point $P$ is inside $\triangle{ABC}$, such that $PA=11$, $PB=7$, and $PC=6$. Legs $\overline{AC}$ and $\overline{BC}$ have length $s=\sqrt{a+b\sqrt{2}}$, where $a$ and $b$ are positive integers. What is $a+b$?

[asy]
pair A,B,C,P;
A=(10,0);
B=(0,10);
C=(0,0);
P=(3,3.5);
draw(A--B--C--cycle,linewidth(0.7));
draw(A--P,linewidth(0.7));
draw(B--P--C,linewidth(0.7));
label("$A$",A,E);
label("$B$",B,N);
label("$C$",C,S);
label("$P$",P,NE);
label("7",(1.5,6.75),E);
label("6",(1.5, 1.75),E);
label("11",(6.5,1.75),S);
[/asy]
